            \n                        <section class=\"mt-4 mb-3\"> <h2 id=\"tld-about\" class=\"h5 mb-2\">About .SE</h2><p>.se is the country code top-level domain (ccTLD) for Sweden. It is managed by The Internet Infrastructure Foundation (IIS). The domain is available to anyone wishing to connect their website with Sweden, including individuals, companies, and organizations. Registration is open both to Swedish residents and foreigners, but valid identification is required: for Swedes – a personal ID number, for EU citizens – a VAT or tax ID, and for others – business registration details or a passport. This makes .se a strong choice for highlighting national affiliation and trust, and it is often used by businesses operating in the Swedish market. Alternatives include other Nordic domains such as <a href=\"/no#tld-about\">.no</a>, <a href=\"/dk#tld-about\">.dk</a>, or international domains like <a href=\"/eu#tld-about\">.eu</a> and <a href=\"/com#tld-about\">.com</a>.</p><p class=\"random-tlds\">Random TLDs: &nbsp;<a href=\"/do#tld-about\">.do</a> <a href=\"/tv#tld-about\">.tv</a> <a href=\"/vote#tld-about\">.vote</a> <a href=\"/xin#tld-about\">.xin</a> <a href=\"/flights#tld-about\">.flights</a> <a href=\"/br#tld-about\">.br</a> <a href=\"/earth#tld-about\">.earth</a></p> </section>\n                        \n                        <div class=\"p-2 mb-3 text-center bbottom seeMore-links\" style=\"background-color: #e8f0f8;\"><ul class=\"list-inline mb-0\"><li class=\"list-inline-item\">Popular:</li><li class=\"list-inline-item\"><a href=\"/com\">com</a></li><li class=\"list-inline-item\"><a href=\"/net\">net</a></li><li class=\"list-inline-item\"><a href=\"/org\">org</a></li><li class=\"list-inline-item\"><a href=\"/ai\">ai</a></li><li class=\"list-inline-item\"><a href=\"/info\">info</a></li><li class=\"list-inline-item\"><a href=\"/co\">co</a></li><li class=\"list-inline-item\"><a href=\"/io\">io</a></li><li class=\"list-inline-item\"><a href=\"/xyz\">xyz</a